Women and Migration

Responses in Art and History

Deborah Willis, Ellyn Toscano, Kalia Brooks Nelson (dir.)

Open Book Publishers, 2019

   The essays in this book chart how women's profound and turbulent
   experiences of migration have been articulated in writing, photography,
   art and film. As a whole, the volume gives an impression of a wide
   range of migratory events from women's perspectives, covering the
   Caribbean Diaspora, refugees and slavery through the various lenses of
   politics and war, love and family.

   The contributors, which include academics and artists, offer both
   person...
