A View from Elsewhere on Publishing, Copyright and Creativity

Janis Jefferies, Sarah Kember (dir.)

Open Book Publishers, 2019

   Whose Book is it Anyway? is a provocative collection of essays that
   opens out the copyright debate to questions of open access, ethics, and
   creativity. It includes views — such as artist's perspectives, writer's
   perspectives, feminist, and international perspectives — that are too
   often marginalized or elided altogether.

